race.comment: DOUBT IN THE SKY (12) just missed first-up and then was on speed when winning a Maiden at Dunkeld. She did it well, and doubt this is much harder. Strips fitter and can take the next step. HUGHIE (5) is free running and has been unlucky not to have broken through. He gets in well with the 3kg claim and will go close with average luck skipping across from the awkward gate. THE WIZARD KING (1) rates up to this but has an outside barrier to cope with. Has a handy 3kg claim in easier company and will go close if things work out. BOURBON ROAD (4) peaks and has been knocking on the door. Coffey is reunited, and he's fit enough to manage the longer sprint. He's in the mix as well.
